# Cursor Rules for Notion Agent Hub

## Project Context
This is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that provides Notion integration tools and AI agent workflows. Built with TypeScript, using the MCP SDK for server implementation.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- ES modules (import/export, .js extensions in imports)
- Zod for input validation
- Functional style preferred over classes
- Descriptive variable names, JSDoc comments on exports

## MCP Patterns
- Tools are registered via `server.tool()` with Zod schemas
- Tool handlers return `{ content: [{ type: "text", text: string }] }`
- Errors return `{ content: [...], isError: true }`
- Server uses stdio transport (stdout reserved for MCP)
- All logging goes to stderr via the logger utility

## Notion API
- Use @notionhq/client for all Notion operations
- Singleton client via `getNotionClient()`
- Handle rich_text arrays with `richTextToPlain()` / `plainToRichText()`
- Page properties vary by type — check `prop.type` before accessing
- Database queries support filters, sorts, and pagination

## File Organization
- `src/tools/` — Individual MCP tools (one per file)
- `src/agents/` — Agent workflows that compose tools
- `src/queue/` — Task queue for Notion DB polling
- `src/utils/` — Shared utilities (Notion client, logger)
- `tests/tools/` — Vitest unit tests with mocked Notion client

## Testing
- Use vitest for testing
- Mock the Notion client in tests (vi.mock)
- Test tool functions directly, not MCP handlers
- Each tool has its own test file

## Environment Variables
- NOTION_API_KEY — Required for Notion operations
- NOTION_DATABASE_ID — Default database for task queue
- OPENAI_API_KEY — Optional, for content generation
- BRAVE_API_KEY — Optional, for web search
- LOG_LEVEL — debug | info | warn | error (default: info)
